#4302
Deep within the fissure~
Deep within the fissure's black embrace, the hand holds allowing one to
climb become more sparse and treacherous.  Black soot makes the walls
slippery while some of the fragments crumble to dust at the touch of a hand.
Light from far above seems to be almost eaten by the blackness.  An erie feeling
ebbs from the walls, wounded like a hurt animal, cringing from the sightest
touch.
~
